import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.hist(column='source', bins=50, alpha=0.5, label='Source')
    data.hist(column='target', bins=50, alpha=0.5, label='Target')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Dependencies')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of module dependencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    source_module_count = data['source'].value_counts().nlargest(10)
    ax = source_module_count.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Source Module ID')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common source module for dependencies?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['num_dependencies'] = data.groupby('source')['target'].transform('count')
    plt.boxplot(data['num_dependencies'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average number of dependencies per module?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['num_dependencies'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
